avatar/050383609de22149103fd61a3cb41442?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/050383609de22149103fd61a3cb41442?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/tinocm/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">tinocm</a> il <span class=\"review-date\">Maggio 27, 2024</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I started using woocomerce recently and it is really good!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">joke</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 su 5 stelle\" data-title-template=\"%s su 5 stelle\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Di <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/botchco/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/e9bcbb5fd9b143266e27b0da9514a7fb?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/e9bcbb5fd9b143266e27b0da9514a7fb?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/botchco/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">botchco</a> il <span class=\"review-date\">Maggio 27, 2024</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>the fact that you can\'t even change the name of your store is laughable. how long was this developed not to have such a basic option...</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>No workaround are even good for this, custom functions, seo plugins, changing shop title in the shop title section - nothing. You don\'t decide how to call your store, woocommerce does. And it will be called \"Shop\" until the end of time. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Shopify it is</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Quick help</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 su 5 stelle\" data-title-template=\"%s su 5 stelle\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Di <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/al24/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/dccb1a12ca1e08b9c4b4d74dbbdbbec3?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/dccb1a12ca1e08b9c4b4d74dbbdbbec3?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/al24/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">al24</a> il <span class=\"review-date\">Maggio 19, 2024</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I am positively surprised by the quick help and simple enough advice! Thank you!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Good support</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"4 su 5 stelle\" data-title-template=\"%s su 5 stelle\" data-rating=\"4\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Di <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/jaroslawistok/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/b8a290a57e56699baaf9a13c0a3da84b?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/b8a290a57e56699baaf9a13c0a3da84b?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/jaroslawistok/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">jaroslawistok</a> il <span class=\"review-date\">Maggio 16, 2024</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Good support but still many issues.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Always redirects to its own ad</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 su 5 stelle\" data-title-template=\"%s su 5 stelle\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Di <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/birblogcu/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/3c62ddb21fcb596bcfd7bd43aa5a8bf9?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/3c62ddb21fcb596bcfd7bd43aa5a8bf9?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/birblogcu/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">birblogcu</a> il <span class=\"review-date\">Maggio 15, 2024</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I manage a multisite and have clients migrating from other ecommerce platforms. But with every update, woocommerce sends a notification in the complete installation panel and redirects to the plugins page and tries to sell something to the users. It also always encourages creating a wordpress.com account. This causes confusion for my customers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Don\'t you think why this might be a multisite network? They don\'t have access to everything, and uninformed users encounter errors all the time. Sponsored add-ons are even suggested in the installation wizard.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Please consider users with multisite networks. It\'s not too difficult for developers to think of this.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Great Plugin</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 su 5 stelle\" data-title-template=\"%s su 5 stelle\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"sta